titles: The Dutchess of Portsmouths farewel: the Dutchess holds a dialogue, yea, doth relate the wretched state, and talks with Madam Gwin; that now she liveth in. To the tune of, Tan tarra rara tan tivee.
publisher: printed for I. Clarke, W. Thackeray, and T. passinger [sic],
notes: Place and date of publication suggested by Wing.
Verse: "I Prithee dear Portsmouth now tell my thy mind ..."
Reproduction of original in the British Library.
keywords: Kéroualle, Louise-Renée de, --  Duchess of Portsmouth and Aubigny, 1649-   1734 --  Poetry --  Early works to 1800.
